The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) for power allocation in multi-user wireless communication cellular networks. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields, including machine learning (ML), networking and communications (NI), information theory (IT), systems and control (SY), and artificial intelligence (AI). Given that the paper focuses on the use of DRL, which is a subfield of ML, and its application to wireless networks, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, it also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, since DRL is a subfield of AI, it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
